‘The body of the blastostyle is usually considerably dilated and has a superficial resemblance to a simple ovoid sporosac’. ‘The medusoid structure of the gonosome is completely reduced in the male, … The sperm cells (fig. 33 , sp .) are found in a dense cluster between the ectoderm and endoderm even in the youngest blastostyles we have examined ( 0.1 mm in length), and neither in these nor in the older blastostyles can we find any true medusoid structures.’ (
Hickson & Gravely 1907 : 9
